1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,280
Hi, good afternoon.

2
00:00:04,280 --> 00:00:09,720
This is a short tutorial on how to use the new CBVMI app.

3
00:00:09,720 --> 00:00:12,960
I will first show the online version of the app.

4
00:00:16,520 --> 00:00:21,480
So as you might know, we have two versions for this VMI app.

5
00:00:21,480 --> 00:00:22,880
One is for online.

6
00:00:22,880 --> 00:00:25,480
One is for offline.

7
00:00:25,480 --> 00:00:29,880
Online is only to be used if the customer

8
00:00:29,880 --> 00:00:33,040
your VMI customer has good internet connection,

9
00:00:33,040 --> 00:00:36,320
stable internet connection on the site.

10
00:00:36,320 --> 00:00:38,040
If that is not the case,

11
00:00:38,040 --> 00:00:41,520
if the customer does not have stable internet connection,

12
00:00:41,520 --> 00:00:44,560
then we want to go with the offline mode.

13
00:00:45,760 --> 00:00:47,680
So here, as you can see,

14
00:00:47,680 --> 00:00:49,520
the first screen is the login screen

15
00:00:49,520 --> 00:00:52,600
when you open the CBVMI app.

16
00:00:52,600 --> 00:00:56,280
The first thing you want to do is select the user ID.

17
00:00:56,280 --> 00:00:58,520
So for this example, we will be selecting

18
00:00:58,520 --> 00:01:01,200
Maryland Tremblay as the user ID.

19
00:01:01,200 --> 00:01:03,720
So you can see MNTY.

20
00:01:03,720 --> 00:01:07,840
And the next step is to enter the password.

21
00:01:07,840 --> 00:01:10,520
So by default, for everybody,

22
00:01:10,520 --> 00:01:15,520
the password is set as 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 6 digit number.

23
00:01:18,360 --> 00:01:20,440
We also have option to change password.

24
00:01:20,440 --> 00:01:24,200
As you can see here, you can change password

25
00:01:24,200 --> 00:01:26,160
as per your liking.

26
00:01:26,160 --> 00:01:30,520
But for this example, we will go with the default password.

27
00:01:30,520 --> 00:01:32,200
So we login as Maryland

28
00:01:32,200 --> 00:01:36,640
and we enter the password 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6 and login.

29
00:01:37,920 --> 00:01:41,720
Here, you are on the main home screen of the app.

30
00:01:41,720 --> 00:01:45,640
And your first option here is for online order.

31
00:01:45,640 --> 00:01:50,640
So we click that and you will see the spade here.

32
00:01:50,880 --> 00:01:54,240
We are only going to select order management,

33
00:01:54,240 --> 00:01:57,400
which is the first tab shown here.

34
00:01:57,400 --> 00:01:59,600
Other tabs are not required at this point.

35
00:02:00,560 --> 00:02:03,400
Here, as you can see, you have all the customers

36
00:02:04,360 --> 00:02:05,520
for that user ID.

37
00:02:05,520 --> 00:02:07,560
So for example, for Maryland,

38
00:02:07,560 --> 00:02:10,320
she works with all the Quebec accounts.

39
00:02:10,320 --> 00:02:13,800
So she will only be able to see all the VMI accounts

40
00:02:13,800 --> 00:02:15,480
from the Quebec region.

41
00:02:15,480 --> 00:02:18,560
So as you can see, all the RFP sites are here.

42
00:02:20,240 --> 00:02:23,600
We will select RFP Doble for this example.

43
00:02:24,400 --> 00:02:28,560
You can also see the search bar shown here above.

44
00:02:28,560 --> 00:02:30,080
This is like a Google search.

45
00:02:30,080 --> 00:02:33,840
So basically, if you don't want to scroll down the list manually

46
00:02:33,840 --> 00:02:37,400
and you know the customer that you are looking to do the scan for,

47
00:02:37,400 --> 00:02:39,680
you just enter the customer number here.

48
00:02:39,680 --> 00:02:43,840
So 3, 9, 0, 0, 2 and you're going to see RFP Doble.

49
00:02:43,840 --> 00:02:46,400
Or if you want to type with the letters,

50
00:02:46,400 --> 00:02:50,400
you can type D-O-L, B-E-A and you see the customer there.

51
00:02:51,440 --> 00:02:52,960
And you select the customer,

52
00:02:55,200 --> 00:02:59,920
and you select the ship to that you want to start scanning for that customer.

53
00:02:59,920 --> 00:03:03,680
So for this example, we're going to select VMI1 main store.

54
00:03:03,680 --> 00:03:09,280
And when you are in this screen, you can see the inventory loaded

55
00:03:09,280 --> 00:03:11,760
for that ship to for the customer.

56
00:03:11,760 --> 00:03:15,600
So all items here showing for VMI1 for RFP Doble.

57
00:03:16,880 --> 00:03:19,520
Here you can see on the search bar shown above,

58
00:03:20,400 --> 00:03:22,320
you can enter the CPN number.

59
00:03:22,320 --> 00:03:26,480
So you can enter D-B-1523.

60
00:03:27,120 --> 00:03:31,120
And it's going to only show you the one item for that CPN.

61
00:03:31,120 --> 00:03:33,760
You can also use CB part number.

62
00:03:33,760 --> 00:03:40,240
So 462055B-F.

63
00:03:40,240 --> 00:03:43,360
So it's a Brighton Best part and it's going to show you that.

64
00:03:43,360 --> 00:03:49,120
So it's like a Google search where you can use to search for the item

65
00:03:49,120 --> 00:03:49,920
that you want to scan.

66
00:03:51,600 --> 00:03:56,400
If you want to use the camera, you also have the option of opening the scan option here.

67
00:03:56,960 --> 00:03:59,440
And we'll ask you to access your camera.

68
00:03:59,440 --> 00:04:03,200
You say allow and you will have the bar code here.

69
00:04:03,200 --> 00:04:07,760
And you can scan the label and it will pick up the CPN from the label

70
00:04:08,320 --> 00:04:11,280
and populate it in the search bar shown above.

71
00:04:12,160 --> 00:04:18,080
So two options, you can either do scan with the camera or you can enter manually the CPN number here.

72
00:04:18,880 --> 00:04:24,800
For example, D-B-1523 and you're going to see that one item there.

73
00:04:26,720 --> 00:04:29,040
For this example, I'm going to select two items.

74
00:04:29,040 --> 00:04:30,720
So I'm going to do the first item here.

75
00:04:30,720 --> 00:04:35,120
I enter a quantity, let's say we want to order 100 of this item.

76
00:04:35,760 --> 00:04:41,520
When you enter the quantity in this box, please make sure that you check this order quantity box.

77
00:04:42,320 --> 00:04:45,040
If you do not check or if you forget to check this box,

78
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:50,000
this item will not be added to the shopping cart, which I will show you in the next step.

79
00:04:50,560 --> 00:04:55,440
So it's very important to check this box for the item that you want to order.

80
00:04:56,160 --> 00:04:57,440
So we ordered one item now.

81
00:04:57,440 --> 00:04:58,400
We're going to order one more.

82
00:04:58,400 --> 00:05:02,320
We're going to scan this item and we're going to say we want 50 of this item.

83
00:05:02,880 --> 00:05:05,200
And again, make sure you check box here.

84
00:05:05,840 --> 00:05:07,200
So we have two items here.

85
00:05:07,840 --> 00:05:11,520
And let's say that is all that I want to scan for this customer.

86
00:05:12,080 --> 00:05:16,480
So as you can see on the bottom right corner, I click on the shopping cart icon.

87
00:05:17,200 --> 00:05:22,720
When I click on the shopping cart, it takes me to the next screen where I can review any item.

88
00:05:22,720 --> 00:05:27,200
If I want to change or if I want to delete, I can click on the delete option and delete the item.

89
00:05:28,160 --> 00:05:29,680
And review everything.

90
00:05:29,680 --> 00:05:35,600
If everything is good, you click on review on the left bottom corner of your screen.

91
00:05:36,400 --> 00:05:41,200
And this takes you to the final order screen, where it gives you one more chance to look

92
00:05:41,760 --> 00:05:43,280
and check if everything is good.

93
00:05:43,920 --> 00:05:46,400
If everything is good, you send the order.

94
00:05:47,680 --> 00:05:50,720
Also, you have an option to make it urgent or normal.

95
00:05:50,720 --> 00:05:56,080
So right now, by default, it is normal, but you can also make it urgent by clicking on this

96
00:05:56,080 --> 00:05:59,040
toggle and it will send you high importance email.

97
00:05:59,680 --> 00:06:08,720
And I place order, I click on order, here, and give it maybe 10 or 20 seconds.

98
00:06:12,080 --> 00:06:12,480
Yes.

99
00:06:12,480 --> 00:06:22,320
So as you can see here, on the top of your screen, you have a message saying order,

100
00:06:22,320 --> 00:06:24,240
placed, and email sent successfully.

101
00:06:24,960 --> 00:06:33,360
Now, if you check your outlook email, you're going to see the order in your email,

102
00:06:33,360 --> 00:06:34,880
in your inbox, just like this.

103
00:06:34,880 --> 00:06:36,720
So I place the order at 301.

104
00:06:36,720 --> 00:06:42,240
At 301 p.m., I get the email from the app saying that I have placed the VMI order,

105
00:06:42,240 --> 00:06:45,920
customer number, ship two, and customer name.

106
00:06:45,920 --> 00:06:48,400
And here you can see the order details.

107
00:06:48,400 --> 00:06:50,240
You have all the important information here,

108
00:06:51,760 --> 00:06:59,120
order date, order time, quantity, bin location, CB part number, and the person who placed the

109
00:06:59,120 --> 00:07:00,720
order, in this case, it was mean.

110
00:07:01,280 --> 00:07:09,120
So, and once we have this app connected with NetSuite, the final step is after this email,

111
00:07:09,120 --> 00:07:14,240
you're going to get another email from NetSuite for the quote request that is created for this order.

112
00:07:14,800 --> 00:07:21,040
And with the QU quotation number, and you will use that to log into NetSuite to process that order

113
00:07:21,040 --> 00:07:25,680
for the customer, like you currently do for your VMI customers.

114
00:07:26,320 --> 00:07:28,640
So this was for the online orders.

